Reporter THE average water levels for dams across the Eastern Cape province have decreased slightly during the past week and are currently sitting at 67.9%. According to the Department of Water and Sanitation, the water crisis remains critical in Nelson Mandela Bay (NMB). The water storage levels in dams across the NMB was below 35% last week. At this time last year it was 38.2%. The Algoa Water Supply System, with five major dams serving the area of NMB, is struggling, with the exception of Loerie Dam sitting at 93.5%. The Department of Water and Sanitation is urging residents in the province to use water sparingly and for all sectors to adhere to water restrictions that are in place. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  